Sentencas: We fabricated anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells using decalcomania paper.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties related to the thickness control of the solid oxide fuel cell component layer using decalcomania paper

Sentencas: To investigate the changes in thickness of the component layer and electrical properties in a unit cell, the number of layers of cathodes and the electrolyte decalcomania paper is changed.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties related to the thickness control of the solid oxide fuel cell component layer using decalcomania paper

Sentencas: As a result, the thickness of the electrolyte and cathode layer regularly increases with an increase in the number of decalcomania papers attached.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties related to the thickness control of the solid oxide fuel cell component layer using decalcomania paper

Sentencas: In addition, when only one electrolyte decalcomania paper is attached to an anode support, a tight and dense 8 mu m electrolyte layer is obtained.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties related to the thickness control of the solid oxide fuel cell component layer using decalcomania paper

Sentencas: A unit cell with a cathode thickness of 120 mu m to which decalcomania paper is attached nine times is shown to have an open circuit voltage (OCV) of 1.08 V and a maximum power density (MPD) of 902 mW cm(-2) at 800 A degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical properties related to the thickness control of the solid oxide fuel cell component layer using decalcomania paper
